style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 26pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman"><BR=20
style=3D"PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always" clear=3Dall></SPAN>
<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: =
black"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV>
<TABLE height=3D391 cellSpacing=3D0 cellPadding=3D0 width=3D359 =
vspace=3D"0" hspace=3D"0">
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TD=20
    style=3D"PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; =
PADDING-TOP: 0in"=20
    vAlign=3Dtop align=3Dleft height=3D391>
      <P class=3DStyle3 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 173.55pt 0pt 0.25pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">ABOUT THE AUTHOR </SPAN></P>
      <P class=3DStyle4 style=3D"MARGIN-LEFT: 0.7pt; LINE-HEIGHT: =
10.9pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">Richard Dawkins was born in =
Nairobi in=20
      1941. He was educated at Oxford University, and after graduation =
remained=20
      there to work </SPAN><B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Bold">for=20
      </SPAN></B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">his doctorate =
with the=20
      Nobel Prize-winning ethologist Niko Tinbergen. From 1967 to 1969 =
he was an=20
      Assistant Professor of Zoology at the University of California at=20
      Berkeley. In 1970 he became a Lecturer in Zoology at Oxford =
University and=20
      a Fellow of New College. In 1995 he became the first Charles =
Simonyi=20
      Professor of the Public Understanding of Science at Oxford =
University.=20
      </SPAN></P>
      <P class=3DStyle4=20
      style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.5pt 0pt 0.7pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 10.9pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">Richard Dawkins's first book.=20
      </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">The Selfish =
Gene=20
      </SPAN></I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">(1976; second =
edition,=20
      1989), became an immediate international bestseller and, like=20
      </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">The Blind =
Watchmaker,=20
      </SPAN></I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">was translated =
into all=20
      the major languages. Its sequel, </SPAN><I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">The Extended Phenotype, =
</SPAN></I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">followed in 1982. His other =
bestsellers=20
      include </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">River =
Out of=20
      Eden </SPAN></I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">(1995) =
and=20
      </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Climbing Mount =

      Improbable </SPAN></I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Roman">(1996;=20
      Penguin, 1997). </SPAN></P>
      <P class=3DStyle4=20
      style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.5pt 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.25pt; LINE-HEIGHT: =
10.85pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">Richard Dawkins won both the =
Royal=20
      Society of Literature Award and the Los </SPAN><I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Angeles Times </SPAN></I><SPAN =

      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">Literary Prize in 1987 for=20
      </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">The Blind =
<SPAN=20
      style=3D"COLOR: #bfbfbf">Watchmaker. </SPAN></SPAN></I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">The television film of the =
book, shown in=20
      the </SPAN><I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Horizon=20
      </SPAN></I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Roman">series, won =
the Sci-Tech=20
      Prize for the Best Science Programme of 1987. He has also won the =
1989=20
      Silver Medal of the Zoological Society of London and the 1990 =
Royal=20
      Society Michael Faraday Award for the furtherance of the public=20
      understanding of science. In 1994 he won the Nakayama Prize for =
Human=20
      Science and has been awarded an Honorary D.Litt. by the University =
of St=20
      Andrews and by the Australian National University, Canberra. =
</SPAN></P>
      <P class=3DStyle4=20
      style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.5pt 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0.25pt; LINE-HEIGHT: =
10.85pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Roman"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></DIV><BR=20
clear=3Dall>
