<P class=3DMsoNormal><SPAN style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: =
black"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV>
<TABLE height=3D557 cellSpacing=3D0 cellPadding=3D0 width=3D378 =
vspace=3D"0" hspace=3D"0">
  <TBODY>
  <TR>
    <TD=20
    style=3D"PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; =
PADDING-TOP: 0in"=20
    vAlign=3Dtop align=3Dleft height=3D557>
      <H3 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 86.1pt 0pt 85.45pt"><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 14.5pt">BIBLIOGRAPHY </SPAN><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 9pt"><BR><BR><BR><BR></SPAN></H3>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN-LEFT: 5.3pt">1. Alberts, B., =
Bray, D.,=20
      Lewis, J., Raff, M., Roberts, K. &amp; Watson, J. D. (1983) =
<I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Molecular Biology of the Cell. =

      </SPAN></I>New York: Garland. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22=20
      style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.05pt 0pt 4.3pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 9.9pt">2. =
Anderson, D.=20
      M. (1981) Role of interfacial water and water in thin films in the =
origin=20
      of life. In J. Billingham (ed.) <I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Life in the Universe.=20
      </SPAN></I>Cambridge, Mass: MIT Press. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.45pt 0pt 3.85pt">3. =
Andersson, M.=20
      (1982) Female choice <B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Bold">selects for=20
      extreme </SPAN></B>tail length <B><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Bold">in=20
      a </SPAN></B>widow bird. <I><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Nature, 299: =
</SPAN></I>818-20. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22=20
      style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.15pt 0pt 4.1pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 9.8pt">4. =
Arnold, S. J.=20
      (1983) Sexual selection: the interface of theory <B><SPAN=20
      style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Bold">and </SPAN></B>empiricism. In P. =
P. G.=20
      Bateson (ed.), <I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Mate =
Choice,=20
      </SPAN></I>pp. 67-107. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 34.55pt 0pt 3.85pt">5. =
Asimov, 1.=20
      (1957) <I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">Only a =
Trillion.=20
      </SPAN></I>London: Abelard-Schuman. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 36.45pt 0pt 0.05in">6. =
Asimov, I.=20
      (1980) <I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: =
Times-Italic">Extraterrestrial=20
      Civilizations. </SPAN></I>London: Pan. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 19.2pt 0pt 3.85pt">7. =
Asimov, I.=20
      (1981) <I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">In the =
Beginning.=20
      </SPAN></I>London: New English Library. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 42.45pt 0pt 0.05in">8. =
Atkins, P. W.=20
      (1981) <I><SPAN style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: Times-Italic">The Creation.=20
      </SPAN></I>Oxford: W. H. Freeman. </P>
      <P class=3DStyle22 style=3D"MARGIN: 0in 0.75pt 0pt 3.35pt">9. =
